                                                          {\"model_output\": \"ModelOutput(text=\\\"Startpage is a privacy-focused search engine that has gained attention for its commitment to user anonymity and data protection. Here are some key points you might consider including in your article:\\\\n\\\\n### Overview\\\\n- **Founding and Purpose**: Startpage was founded in 2006 and is based in the Netherlands. Its primary goal is to provide users with a search experience that prioritizes privacy, allowing them to search the web without being tracked or having their personal data collected.\\\\n\\\\n### Privacy Features\\\\n- **No Tracking**: Startpage does not track user searches or store personal information. This means that users can search the web without worrying about their data being sold or used for targeted advertising.\\\\n- **Anonymous Search**: Startpage allows users to search anonymously by acting as an intermediary between the user and the search results. This means that the search queries are not linked to the user's IP address.\\\\n- **No Cookies**: The search engine does not use cookies to track user behavior, further enhancing privacy.\\\\n\\\\n### Search Results\\\\n- **Google Results**: Startpage provides search results powered by Google, which means users can access high-quality search results while maintaining their privacy. This unique feature sets Startpage apart from other privacy-focused search engines that may not offer the same level of result quality.\\\\n- **Customizable Interface**: Users can customize their search experience with various settings, including language preferences and search filters.\\\\n\\\\n### Additional Features\\\\n- **Startpage Proxy**: This feature allows users to view websites anonymously by routing their connection through Startpage's servers. This adds an extra layer of privacy when visiting sites.\\\\n- **Mobile App**: Startpage offers a mobile app for both Android and iOS, making it easy for users to mainta